Amazing, this app works spot-on with all my coins. Gold and silver testing equipment can add up in cost. This test costs very little yet is one of the best for detecting the flood of counterfeits out there on the market. This is one great tool in your belt while you still do all the other simple tests such as measuring, weighing, specific gravity, resistance, acid, magnetic slide and the Ping test this takes the Ping test to the next level. I hope the app is expanded soon to include the smaller denominations as well!

Received shipment of 1 oz buffalo coins from JM Bouillon . Each one failed test . Never had problem with app before . Specific gravity of coins was measured at 10.62 slightly above the 10.50 standard . What's up ???
replyContent:
Buffalos are sometimes tricky, because there are so many different manufacturers making them.
Note that there are two different types of Buffalo coins in the app. Did you select the correct one?
While the frequency diagram is showing in the app, select "Support" in the menu. This will send me a screenshot, so I can have a look at what is going on.

Significant wear and tear on old coins can throw off the sound just a little bit. As can the lower manufacturing accuracy of very old coins.

Support for the Sunshine Mint (SMI) silver buffalo with reeded edge has now been added to the app.

content: Gold Maple Leaf coin thickness data is missing. Also it be great to have some control over the microphone sensitivity.
replyContent:
The Gold Maple Leaf thickness data is missing because the Canadian mint does not officially specify any particular thickness, as far as I know.

The app actually has automatic input sensitivity. But a few Android devices have poor microphones, and I have been unable to find a workaround for that.
